"16667","5/6/2004 14:49","04MADRID1601","Embassy Madrid","CONFIDENTIAL","04STATE99626","This record is a partial extract of the original cable. The full text of the original cable is not available.


 ","C O N F I D E N T I A L MADRID 001601 
 
SIPDIS 
 
E.O. 12958: DECL: 05/05/2014 
TAGS: PREL, KPAL, IS, SP, UNGA 
SUBJECT: SPAIN: URGENT DEMARCHE REGARDING AMENDED UNGA 
RESOLUTION ON PALESTINIAN OBSERVER MISSION STATUS 
 
REF: STATE 99626 
 
Classified By: Kathleen Fitzpatrick, Political Counselor for Reasons 1. 
4 (b) and (d) 
 
(C) We delivered reftel demarche to Inigo de Palacio, MFA 
Director of UN Affairs, on May 5.  De Palacio stated at the 
time that Spain was still looking with interest at whether 
the Palestinians would accept the EU\'s suggested changes to 
the resolution.  He said that the matter was one of personal 
interest to Spanish FM Moratinos (who was in Dublin for the 
Euro-Mediterranean Ministerial Conference), and that the MFA 
would receive its orders on how to vote directly from him. 
De Palacio later phoned us on May 6 to say that the great 
majority of EU countries were in favor of voting for the 
amended Palestinian resolution and that Spain would vote in 
favor or abstain on the resolution, though the final decision 
had not yet been reached.  We will update with any further 
developments. 
ARGYROS 
