SUBJECT: SPAIN: POSITIVE ABOUT U.S. VIEWS ON IRAN/IAEA 
 
REF: STATE 122673 
 
Classified By: KATHLEEN M. FITZPATRICK, POLITICAL COUNSELOR. 
REASON 1.4 (B) & (D) 
 
(C) We discussed reftel points on June 9 with Marcos 
Rodriguez Cantero in the Foreign Ministry\'s Office of 
International Disarmament Affairs.  Rodriguez said Spain 
welcomes U.S. views on the June IAEA DG report and agrees 
with the need for a strong resolution on Iran at the upcoming 
IAEA Board of Governor\'s meeting.  He said Spain\'s ambassador 
in Vienna is working with other EU ambassadors to draft a 
response to the DG report and is considering next steps on 
Iran-IAEA issues. 
