E.O. 12958: DECL: 06/10/2014 
TAGS: KNNP, PARM, PREL, MNUC, TRGY, SP, Non-Proliferation Issues 
SUBJECT: SPAIN AGREES ON U.S VIEWS TO STRENGTHEN IAEA 
 
REF: STATE 125606 
 
Classified By: POLITICAL COUNSELOR, KATHLEEN M. FITZPATRICK. 
REASON 1.4 (B) & (D) 
 
(C) We discussed reftel points with Marcos Rodriguez Cantero 
at the MFA Office of International Disarmament Affairs on 
June 9.  Rodriguez will be a member of Spain\'s delegation to 
the June 14-18 IAEA boarding meeting.  Rodriguez said that 
Spain favored: encouraging states to sign and ratify the IAEA 
Additional Protocol; creating a Special Committee on 
Safeguards; and prohibiting states under investigation for 
proliferation violations from serving on the Board of 
Governors. 
