Spain had sent a delegation of defense officials to meet with 
the former defense minister after President Karzai decided to 
drop him from the election ticket.  Morales said that he had 
not seen a read-out on the delegation\'s meeting, but he did 
not expect that President Karzai\'s decision would deter Spain 
from fulfilling its commitment to sending troops and, and 
possibly, civilian volunteers to assist in Afghanistan\'s 
presidential elections in September.  Morales stated that 
Spain shares our desire to promote stability and democratic 
reform in Afghanistan in the support of the Afghani people. 
