SUBJECT: SPAIN: MOLDOVA/TRANSNISTRIA RESPONSE 
 
REF: STATE 169792 
 
Classified By: Kathleen Fitzpatrick, Political Counselor. 
Reasons 1.4 (B) & (D). 
 
(C)  Poloff delivered reftel demarche concerning growing 
tensions in Moldova August 10 to Marta Ruiz, desk officer for 
Eastern and Central Europe at the Spanish Foreign Ministry. 
Ruiz replied that Spain favored the five-sided talks that 
included EU and U.S. participation and was optimistic that a 
new Russian envoy was now involved in the mediation efforts. 
She was unsure whether Spain\'s mission in Moscow was 
discussing the issue bilaterally with Russian counterparts. 
Ruiz told Poloff that she would relate our points to others 
in the MFA and to the Spanish mission in Russia.  We will 
report any further GOS reaction. 
MANZANARES 
