 ","C O N F I D E N T I A L MADRID 004486 
 
SIPDIS 
 
DEPARTMENT FOR EUR/ERA, EUR/WE, STAS, EAP/J, AND OES/SAT 
 
E.O. 12958: DECL: 11/24/2014 
TAGS: TNGD, TRGY, TSPL, ENRG, PREL 
SUBJECT: SPAIN CONTINUES TO SUPPORT SIX-PARTY ITER FRAMEWORK 
 
REF: A. SECSTATE 249727 
     B. MADRID 4427 AND PREVIOUS 
 
Classified By: ECONCOUNS WHITNEY BAIRD PER 1.4 (B/D) 
 
(C)  ESTHOFF made Ref A points November 24 to Science 
Ministry Technology Policy Director General Carlos Alejaldre 
Losilla, underscoring U.S. commitment to the six-party ITER 
framework and urging Spain to argue within EU deliberations 
in favor of the six-party framework and against any 
unilateral action.  Alejaldre, who will lead the Spanish 
delegation during the ITER discussions at the November 25-6 
Brussels meeting of the EU Competitiveness Council, told 
ESTHOFF that his views had not changed since he had met with 
ESTHOFF November 12 to discuss ITER and other matters (see 
Ref B).  Alejaldre reiterated that Spain will argue 
strenuously within the EU to maintain the six-party 
framework.  He underscored, however, that Spain would of 
course support whatever decision emerges from the November 
25-6 meetings. 
MANZANARES 
